.TH "pty_common_install" 9 "pty_common_install" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pty_common_install \- set up the pty pair
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pty_common_install
.BI "(struct tty_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "struct tty_struct *tty "  ","
.BI "bool legacy "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "driver" 12
the pty driver
.IP "tty" 12
the tty being instantiated
.IP "legacy" 12
true if this is BSD style

Perform the initial set up for the tty/pty pair. Called from the
tty layer when the port is first opened.

Locking: the caller must hold the tty_mutex
